Durban - Fifteen children are recovering after the vehicle they were travelling in left the roadway in Clermont on Sunday. According to Garrith Jamieson from Rescue Care paramedics, the vehicle transporting the children aged between 5 and 10 years left the roadway and went down an embankment in 4th Avenue just after lunch. "When paramedics arrived on scene they were shown to a nearby house where they found fifteen children aged between 5 years old and 10 years old who had been on the rear of the bakkie had sustained minor injuries. "Immediately more ambulances were dispatched to the scene to assist. Once all fifteen had been stabilised they were transported to a nearby clinic for further care. At this stage the events leading up to the collision is unknown." Jamieson said SAPS were on scene. Two people were killed in two separate collisions on the M7 in Pinetown in the early hours of Monday morning. Daily News